SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 109
BY SENATOR STINE
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH. Recognizes Monday, May 11, 2026 as Louisiana Arts
Day in Louisiana.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To recognize Monday, May 11, 2026, as Louisiana Arts Day in Louisiana.
3 WHEREAS, the state of Louisiana is known for its rich and diverse cultural heritage,
4 shaped by generations of artists, musicians, writers, performers, and tradition bearers whose
5 creativity defines the spirit and identity of our people; and
6 WHEREAS, Louisiana's arts and culture sector is a vital economic engine, generating
7 an estimated six billion six hundred million dollars in annual economic impact, supporting
8 more than forty-nine thousand jobs, and contributing approximately two point one percent
9 to the state's gross domestic product; and
10 WHEREAS, artists and cultural workers in this state are the driving force behind the
11 state's thriving tourism industry, attracting millions of visitors each year who come to
12 experience the state's unique music, cuisine, festivals, visual arts, historic sites, and cultural
13 traditions; and
14 WHEREAS, Louisiana tourism is powered by the creativity, innovation, and
15 authenticity of Louisiana's artists and culture bearers, whose work not only enriches the lives
16 of residents but also strengthens communities and local economies across all sixty-four
17 parishes; and
18 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Partnership for the Arts works to advocate on behalf of
